completed.description:
Add `--format json` output to continueexport.

When `--format json` is passed, instead of calling buildReport() (Markdown), call buildJsonReport() which returns a structured object:

```ts
interface ExportJson {
  meta: { project: string; generated: string; period_days: number; since: string }
  summary: { decisions: number; open_tasks: number; completed_tasks: number; sessions: number; observations: number; questions: number }
  tasks: { open: Task[]; completed: Task[] }
  decisions: Decision[]
  handoffs: Session[]
  observations: Note[]
  plans: Array<Plan & { steps: PlanStep[] }>
  questions: Question[]
}
```

Serialize with JSON.stringify(data, null, 2). File extension should default to .json when --format json is used (override --output default intelligently, but honour explicit --output).

Acceptance: tsc clean; output file is valid JSON that can be parsed back; all keys present even when arrays are empty.
